Sentencas: Mixed-conducting (Bi,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3-delta' (BiSCF) perovskites are considered to be promising candidates for the application as cathode materials in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) operating in the intermediate-temperature regime.
Titulo: Oxygen Exchange Kinetics of (Bi,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3-δ Thin-Film Microelectrodes

Sentencas: In this study, the effective rate constants of surface oxygen exchange of both Co-free and Co-containing BiSCF perovskites were measured by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) on geometrically well-defined thin-film microelectrodes on Y2O3-doped ZrO2 (YSZ) single crystal substrates.
Titulo: Oxygen Exchange Kinetics of (Bi,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3-δ Thin-Film Microelectrodes

Sentencas: Oxygen exchange rate constants in the range of 3.0 x 10(-7) cm s(-1) to 2.4 x 10(-6) cm s(-1) at 750 degrees C and an oxygen partial pressure p(O-2) of 0.2 bar were obtained, which are higher in particular for Co-containing BiSCF than those of La-containing perovskites.
Titulo: Oxygen Exchange Kinetics of (Bi,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3-δ Thin-Film Microelectrodes

Sentencas: The interrelation between the oxygen exchange rate constant and other material properties was investigated to derive information about the oxygen exchange mechanism.
Titulo: Oxygen Exchange Kinetics of (Bi,Sr)(Co,Fe)O3-δ Thin-Film Microelectrodes
